  "text": "Let ðW ; SÞ be a Coxeter system. Following [CITATION_1] we call a set S 0 H W fundamental if ðW ; S 0 Þ is a Coxeter system. In [CITATION_2] it is defined what it means for two fundamental sets to be twist equivalent, see Definition 4.4 of [CITATION_3] or Section 7 below. It is in particular very easy to decide whether for two given fundamental sets there exist twist equivalent sets that have isomorphic Coxeter graphs. Understanding the equivalence classes of fundamental sets of Coxeter groups would therefore solve the isomorphism problem. Our main result is the following:",
